      "content": "interesting. you say it was a failure because of the stability issues, but some people argue it was a success in terms of preventing a massive humanitarian massacre in Benghazi. wouldn't you say the immediate prevention of that kind of violence is a strategic win in itself, regardless of what happened with the government afterwards?",
